    "body": "Problem: There is no way for a `vim.ui.input` caller to indicate for which scope the input is. As in \"This input is for something at cursor scope\". This information can be useful for `vim.ui.input` implementation to tweak its behavior and presentation:\r\n  - Show different floating window depending on the scope. For example:\r\n    - Near cursor for \"cursor\" scope.\r\n    - At line start for \"line\" scope.\r\n    - In window corner for \"buffer\" and \"window\" scope.\r\n    - In whole editor corner for \"tabpage\" and \"editor\" scope.\r\n  - Navigate through history only for inputs with the same scope.\r\n\r\nSolution: Document new `opts.scope` for `vim.ui.input`. Use it in the codebase.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nRelated to #37511.\r\nSimilar in spirit to #37360.",
    "closed_at": null,
