            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "\r\n> 1\\. This is intentionally has nothing to do with floating windows. It _can_, but it shouldn't.\r\n\r\nAs you mentioned in the PR description:\r\n> Show different floating window depending on the scope.\r\n\r\nDoesn't this clarify the association with floating windows?\r\n\r\n> 2\\. Values of `relative` in `nvim_open_win()` are for UI components, which does not have to be related.\r\n\r\nAs I understand it, `vim.ui.input` is simply a UI component provided as an interface so that plugins can reimplement it by overriding. \r\n\r\n> 3\\. This is closer by its goal to `opts.scope` in `:h vim.diagnostic.Opts.Float`, which uses name `scope`.\r\n\r\nThis is fundamentally different from the `scope` in `vim.diagnostic.Opts.Float`. In that case, `scope` determines the range of diagnostics to be displayed in a newly opened floating window—for example, `cursor` includes diagnostics under the current cursor in the floating window, while `buffer` includes diagnostics from the entire buffer. That seems even further removed from the description here.",
            "commit_id": "c98fc55d3fc81af2fc3e0bb9b727ebbafc726dd4",
            "created_at": "2026-05-03T10:29:38Z",
